[2026-07-04T00:45:00] TASK 2D — PIVOT
Two implementation calls made, both flagged rather than decided
silently:
1. Pause-class -> millisecond mapping (structural ~900ms, sentence
   ~250ms, scaled by 1/speed) lives in this module, not the backend.
   CONTRACTS.md §1 only pins the *category* (`pause_class`); SPEC.md
   §6.4 explicitly leaves the exact ms value to "implementation/
   testing," and Speed is local-only client state (§11.2) the backend
   never sees — so the category->ms->speed-scaled-gap conversion has to
   happen here. This is not re-deriving tokenization or which category a
   gap belongs to (still 1D's exclusive job) — only converting an
   already-decided category into an actual timer duration.
2. §11.2 (mute is Zustand-owned local state) vs §11.3 ("engine exposes
   toggleMute()") read as in tension. Resolved by having the hook accept
   `muted`/`speed` as reactive *inputs* (props) rather than re-declaring
   them as the hook's own state — so the boolean still lives in exactly
   one place (wherever the caller's Zustand store puts it), and the
   engine's only job is applying it to `utterance.volume` live. Also hit
   a newer `eslint-plugin-react-hooks` v7 rule ("no ref access during
   render") that the initially-written mutable-ref-sync-in-render-body
   pattern (`itemsRef.current = items` directly in the hook body) tripped
   on 8 times — moved every such sync into its own `useEffect`, no
   product-behavior change, all internal to this file.
3. Title/metadata line text has no pinned CONTRACTS.md shape yet (that's
   Tier 3's job) — kept `PlaybackItem` deliberately generic (`key` +
   `spokenText` + `pauseClass`) so the engine has zero opinion on where
   an item came from; whatever assembles [title, metadata, ...abstract
   segments] (a later integration task) maps CONTRACTS.md's
   `AbstractSegment` plus the eventual title/metadata shape onto this
   list.

