[2026-07-04T00:45:00] TASK 2A — PIVOT
Two pivots worth flagging:
1. Concurrent npm installs (mine adding vite-plugin-pwa/@lhci/cli,
   2C adding msw/@tanstack/react-query, 2C adding zustand) raced in the
   shared frontend/node_modules and produced a broken path-to-regexp
   resolution, then a plain `npm install` I ran to fix it pruned
   msw/@tanstack/react-query/zustand entirely because they weren't yet
   saved to package.json at that moment. Fixed by re-adding all three
   (`@tanstack/react-query`, `zustand` as dependencies; `msw` as
   devDependency) based on what 2C's already-written source files
   (src/api/*, src/state/*) actually import, then re-verified with
   `npm ls` that each dependency tree now carries its own
   non-conflicting path-to-regexp. Full suite green afterward (81/81).
   Flagging for 2C/2D to double check their intended versions match
   what got restored (@tanstack/react-query ^5.101.2, zustand ^5.0.14,
   msw ^2.14.6 — latest at install time, not pinned to anything they'd
   specified since I had no record of their intended versions).
2. SPEC.md §15.5 assumes Lighthouse CI's PWA-installability audits
   (installable-manifest, service-worker, etc.) still exist. They don't:
   Lighthouse v12+ (bundled with the current @lhci/cli@0.15.1) removed
   the entire `pwa` category/audits outright (Chrome's underlying
   installability-error API was deprecated). Rather than silently
   substituting a from-scratch custom check for what SPEC calls "Lighthouse
   CI", pinned `@lhci/cli@0.13.0` (bundles Lighthouse 11.4.0, last version
   with the PWA category intact) so the actual named tool still runs and
   asserts the real installability criteria. Flagging this version pin
   explicitly for Task 5B (CI integration) to confirm/revisit — it's a
   real upstream deprecation, not a workaround I should quietly leave
   undocumented.

