guarded re-entrancy on the `status` *state* value
(`if (status === "playing") return;`), but React state doesn't commit
synchronously within the same tick — two synchronous `play()` calls in
one tick (double-tap, two fast Space keypresses handled in the same
event) both closed over the same not-yet-committed `status` and both
passed the guard, so `env.synth.speak()` was called twice for the same
item (audibly duplicated narration). The generation-counter ref
correctly stopped the *stale* utterance's onend/onerror from corrupting
highlight/finished state afterward, but did nothing to prevent the
second real `speak()` call itself, since both synchronous calls bumped
from and captured the same pre-bump generation. Root cause confirmed by
reverting to the old guard and re-running the new regression test: it
failed exactly as predicted (2 speak() calls instead of 1, then 3 for a
triple-call variant), then restored and re-verified passing.
Fix: added a `statusRef` (a plain ref) as the synchronous source of
truth for `play()`/`pause()`'s re-entrancy guards, updated via a
`setStatusBoth()` helper that writes the ref and calls `setStatus()`
together on every transition (finish/play/pause/cancel) — `status`
(state) is now purely for driving UI re-renders, never read for a
correctness-critical guard. Also added a code comment on the
fire-and-forget `requestWakeLock().then()` in `play()` addressing the
reviewer's separate, unresolved finding (tester's "TASK 2B VERIFY"
mute-test flake hypothesis blaming this promise): confirmed by
inspection this callback only ever writes a plain ref or calls
`lock?.release()`, never touches React state, so it cannot be the
direct cause of a `currentKey`-assertion flake — left as documented and
open per the reviewer's own inconclusive 200+256-iteration repro
attempt, not silently closed.
Worked: added two regression tests under a new "play() re-entrancy"
describe block in usePlaybackEngine.test.ts — `act(() => { play();
play(); })` and a triple-call variant — both assert `speak()` called
exactly once. Confirmed both fail on the pre-fix guard (2/3 calls) and
pass on the fix (1 call). Full suite after the fix: 10/10 in
usePlaybackEngine.test.ts, 83/83 across the whole frontend suite (up
from 81, the 2 new tests), `npx eslint src/playback/` clean, `npx tsc -b
--noEmit` clean, `npm run build` green.
Changed: frontend/src/playback/usePlaybackEngine.ts (statusRef +
setStatusBoth, guard fix, wake-lock comment),
frontend/src/playback/usePlaybackEngine.test.ts (2 new regression
tests). No other files touched.
Open: the intermittent mute-test flake from TASK 2B VERIFY remains
unexplained (not a merge blocker per the coordinator) — documented in
code and in this log for whoever picks it up next; no root cause
identified by either this agent or the adversarial reviewer.

